üìå Assume Table: users
Column	Type
id (PK)	INT AUTO_INCREMENT
name	VARCHAR(50)
email	VARCHAR(50)

simple CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete)

‚úÖ C = CREATE (Insert Record)

INSERT INTO users (name, email)
VALUES ('Ali', 'ali@gmail.com');


üìç R = READ (Select Record)

-- All records:
SELECT * FROM users;

-- Specific record by id:
SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = 1;

-- Specific columns only:
SELECT name, email FROM users;


‚úèÔ∏è U = UPDATE (Edit/Modify Record)

-- Update user where id = 1:
UPDATE users
SET name = 'Ali Khan', email = 'alikhan@gmail.com'
WHERE id = 1;


‚ùå D = DELETE (Remove Record)

-- Delete one record:

DELETE FROM users
WHERE id = 1;

-- Delete all records (use carefully):

DELETE FROM users;




üìç Most Common Used CRUD Queries (1‚Äì2 line each)
Operation	Query
Add user	INSERT INTO users (name, email) VALUES ('Sara','sara@gmail.com');
Show all users	SELECT * FROM users;
Update email	UPDATE users SET email='new@gmail.com' WHERE id=2;
Delete user	DELETE FROM users WHERE id=2;








